# Coding Standards

## TypeScript
- Strict mode only; no `any`
- Explicit return types for public functions
- Use interfaces/type aliases; proper type narrowing

## Linting & Formatting
- ESLint: `@repo/eslint-config`
- Prettier: format on save for `**/*.{ts,tsx,md}`

## Modularity
- One component per file; small, reusable functions
- Backend logic in controllers; routes delegate only

## Error Handling
- Controllers: try/catch, throw typed errors
- Express: central error middleware
- React: Error Boundaries for UI failures
- Next.js: handle fetch errors, use error.tsx and global-error.tsx

## Validation
- Zod `safeParse` for all user/API input
- Validate at API boundary before use

## Next.js Data Fetching
- Server Components: async fetch; use loading.tsx and error.tsx
- Server Actions for mutations; handle errors with toast/UI feedback
